Description: Shoulder sherd of North Ionian Wild Goat style black-figured pottery dinos or krater; inside glazed, the neck black, the body streaky brown; outside: neck worn; on shoulder part of goat grazing to right (horn, part of head, shoulder, with added red); fill of incised rosette and incised blob; incised inscription.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1139)
